1. Fork a repo from repo-server on github

2. Set user.name and user.email
[caoj7@vm1 ~]$ git config --global user.name "jimmycao"
[caoj7@vm1 ~]$ git config --global user.email "jimmy.cao@emc.com"

3. Clone the code from github
[caoj7@vm1 ~]$ git clone https://github.com/jimmycao/slurm.git
git clone https://github.com/jimmycao/Spoon-Knife.git

3. Add upstream and fetch from upstream
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 test]$cd Spoon-Knife/
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git remote add upstream https://github.com/octocat/Spoon-Knife.git

4. Pull in upstream changes  //get upstream's changes and merge into my local disk
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git fetch upstream
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git merge upstream/master

5. Push  commit  //local disk push to my git repo
git add hello.c
git commit â€“m 'first commit'
git push origin master




6. Pull vs fetch/merge
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git pull upstrem

7. Create branch
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git branch mybranch
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git checkout mybranch   //make mybranch active

Operation

[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git checkout master    //make master active
[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git merge mybranch    //merge mybranch into master

[caoj7@cnencaoj7mbp1 Spoon-Knife]$git branch -d mybranch  //delete mybranch

8. PULL request



